==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Par rubber
<hw>Par⟦aacute⟧ rubber</hw>. <def>The caoutchouc obtained from the South
American euphorbiaceous tree <spn>Hevea brasiliensis</spn>, hence called
the Par⟦aacute⟧ rubber tree, from the Brazilian river and seaport named
Par⟦aacute⟧; also, the similar product of other species of
<gen>Hevea</gen>. It is usually exported in flat round cakes, and is a
chief variety of commercial India rubber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parasang</ent>⟦br⟧
